---
layout: base.njk
title: Mike's Second Brain
---
<h1>{{ title }}</h1>
<p class="sub">Senior Director, AI Programs · CodePath</p>

<section class="intro">
  <p>A public-facing view into how I use Claude Cowork and a structured knowledge system at CodePath.</p>
</section>

<section class="metrics-group">
  <h2>Input</h2>
  <p class="group-header">Raw scale. A hoarder's notebook would score just as high, but these numbers answer the first question a new viewer asks: is there actually something here?</p>
  <div class="metrics">
    <div class="metric">
      <div class="label">Day</div>
      <div class="value">{{ metrics.input.days_active }}</div>
      <p class="why">How long the practice has been running. Day 3 means something different from Day 300.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="metric">
      <div class="label">Files tracked</div>
      <div class="value">{{ metrics.input.total_files }}</div>
      <p class="why">Rough size of the knowledge surface. Not a quality signal on its own.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="metric">
      <div class="label">Lines of context</div>
      <div class="value">{{ metrics.input.total_lines }}</div>
      <p class="why">Volume of written thought. Easy to game, but useful as scale.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="metric">
      <div class="label">Total size</div>
      <div class="value">{{ metrics.input.total_kb }} <span class="unit">KB</span></div>
      <p class="why">Same shape as line count, different unit. Different viewers reach for different numbers.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="metrics-group">
  <h2>Activity</h2>
  <p class="group-header">The difference between a practice and a one-time burst. Writing once and stopping produces the same input numbers a few weeks later; these metrics drop to zero.</p>
  <div class="metrics">
    <div class="metric">
      <div class="label">Streak</div>
      <div class="value">{{ metrics.activity.streak_days }} <span class="unit">{% if metrics.activity.streak_days == 1 %}day{% else %}days{% endif %}</span></div>
      <p class="why">Shows whether this is a daily habit or a weekend project.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="metric">
      <div class="label">Topics touched (7d)</div>
      <div class="value">{{ metrics.activity.topics_touched_7d }}</div>
      <p class="why">Breadth of use. Writing in one corner every day is less interesting than working across the whole brain.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="metric">
      <div class="label">Edit:add ratio (30d)</div>
      <div class="value">
        {% if metrics.activity.edit_ratio_pct_30d == null %}—{% else %}{{ metrics.activity.edit_ratio_pct_30d }}<span class="unit">%</span>{% endif %}
      </div>
      <p class="why">Share of recent work that was editing existing notes vs. writing new ones. Separates gardening from hoarding.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="metrics-group">
  <h2>Health</h2>
  <p class="group-header">Maintenance signals. A brain that's never pruned becomes a landfill. These numbers show whether the system is being curated.</p>
  <div class="metrics">
    <div class="metric">
      <div class="label">Staleness</div>
      <div class="value">{{ metrics.health.staleness_pct }}<span class="unit">%</span></div>
      <p class="why">Share of files whose last commit is more than 30 days old. High staleness means accretion without curation.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="metric">
      <div class="label">Knowledge topics</div>
      <div class="value">{{ metrics.health.knowledge_topics }}</div>
      <p class="why">Curated topic files under <code>.claude-memory/topics/</code>. Count grows organically as the brain deepens.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="metric">
      <div class="label">Active projects</div>
      <div class="value">{{ metrics.health.active_projects }}</div>
      <p class="why">Intentional, in-flight work under <code>projects/</code>. Different from knowledge topics — these are things I'm doing, not things I know.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="metric">
      <div class="label">Longest thread</div>
      <div class="value">{{ metrics.health.longest_thread_days }} <span class="unit">{% if metrics.health.longest_thread_days == 1 %}day{% else %}days{% endif %}</span></div>
      <p class="why">
        {% if metrics.health.longest_thread_file %}Longest continuously-updated file is <code>{{ metrics.health.longest_thread_file }}</code>. {% endif %}A long thread is evidence a single line of thought was worked for months, not just drafted once.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="metrics-group">
  <h2>Narrative</h2>
  <p class="group-header">What's alive right now. Static dashboards feel dead. These three fields change whenever the practice does.</p>
  <div class="metrics narrative">
    <div class="metric">
      <div class="label">Most recent topic</div>
      <div class="value value-text">
        {% if metrics.narrative.most_recent_topic %}<code>{{ metrics.narrative.most_recent_topic }}</code>{% else %}—{% endif %}
      </div>
      <p class="why">Top-level path from the latest commit. Gives a sense of what's on my mind without exposing contents.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="metric">
      <div class="label">Last commit</div>
      <div class="value value-text">
        {% if metrics.narrative.last_commit_iso %}<time datetime="{{ metrics.narrative.last_commit_iso }}">{{ metrics.narrative.last_commit_iso | date }}</time>{% else %}—{% endif %}
      </div>
      <p class="why">Lag indicator. If this is days stale, something's wrong.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="metric">
      <div class="label">Latest post</div>
      <div class="value value-text">
        {% if metrics.narrative.latest_post_title %}{{ metrics.narrative.latest_post_title }}{% if metrics.narrative.latest_post_date %} <span class="unit">· {{ metrics.narrative.latest_post_date }}</span>{% endif %}{% else %}—{% endif %}
      </div>
      <p class="why">Connects the private practice to the public output.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="posts">
  <h2>Build log</h2>
  {% set posts = collections.post | reverse %}
  {% if posts.length == 0 %}
    <p class="note">No posts yet.</p>
  {% else %}
    <ul class="post-list">
      {%- for post in posts -%}
        {%- if loop.index0 < 5 %}
        <li>
          <a href="{{ post.url | url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a>
          <span class="post-date"><time datetime="{{ post.date | date('iso') }}">{{ post.date | date }}</time></span>
          {% if post.data.summary %}<p class="post-summary">{{ post.data.summary }}</p>{% endif %}
        </li>
        {% endif -%}
      {%- endfor %}
    </ul>
  {% endif %}
</section>
